A: Though I want to support the argument the others made (split into multiple components), you can already achieve a bit more readability by dropping unnecessary fragments (<></>) and/or parenthesis and by using "better"(opinion) indentation.
return (
  isEnabled
    ? loading
      ? <div><LoadingComponent/></div>
      : items.length === 0
        ? <> {/* this is the only place a fragment is actually needed */}
          <ComponentOne/>
          <Container>
            <img src={Image} alt="Image"/>
          </Container>
        </>
        : <ComponentTwo/>
    : <ComponentThree/>
);


Alternatively, early returns do help a lot with readability. For example:
const SomeComponent = () => {
